This paper deals with the planning and control of a robot in a cluttered environment, which is a common problem in robotics. The use of a harmonic potential field (HPF) is a well-established method in robotics for generating smooth and efficient paths. The paper also discusses the use of HPF-based controllers for both holonomic and nonholonomic robots, which are important topics in robotics. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also deals with control systems and optimization, which are relevant to cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of simulation results suggests that the paper may also be relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CV (Computer Vision).
